# 🎨 Editor Page — Complete UX/UI Redesign Guide
> For the implementer agent. Read every section. Follow in order. No shortcuts.
important read the guide section by section and implement in the order listed — header → sidebar → preview → mode rail → polish. Do NOT let it try to do everything at once.
---

## 🔍 What's Wrong Right Now (Diagnosis)

Looking at the current screenshot and code, here are the **exact problems**:

### 1. Top Header Bar — Cluttered & Overloaded
- Too many items crammed in one row with no visual breathing room
- The "Landing" back button + logo + resume picker + undo/redo + cloud status + export button are all fighting for attention with zero hierarchy
- The `Export PDF` button looks the same weight as other buttons — it should be the **clear primary CTA**
- The `AI Fill Guide` and `ATS Audit` buttons look like unrelated orphan pills
- Dividers (`w-px h-5 bg-border`) are used inconsistently and create visual noise
- Resume name truncates weirdly on medium screens

### 2. Left Sidebar — Generic List, Zero Visual Interest
- The section cards (Contact Info, Work Experience, etc.) look like a plain Android settings list from 2015
- The icon backgrounds (`w-9 h-9 rounded-xl`) are too small and the colors are too muted to create delight
- The "DONE" / "Edit" pills are tiny (`text-[9px]`) and hard to read
- There's no **completion progress indicator** — users have no sense of "how far am I?"
- The section subtitle (preview text) truncates immediately — feels thrown away
- Zero micro-animation on hover — the `hover:bg-zinc-800/50` is barely perceptible
- The sidebar header ("Resume Builder / Click any section to edit") is boring — generic SaaS filler text
- No visual grouping — all 13 sections are dumped in one flat list with just thin border dividers

### 3. Preview Area — Wasted Space & Bad Framing
- The A4 resume preview just floats on `bg-zinc-950` with no visual framing or depth
- There's no "paper" illusion — the resume looks like it's embedded in a dark void
- The zoom level display (`94%`) in the top bar is useful but easy to miss
- The LIVE / HEATMAP toggle at the top of the preview looks disconnected from the preview itself
- Scrolling in the preview area is jarring — no smooth scroll or padding management
- The preview area has no top-right floating actions (like a "fullscreen preview" button)

### 4. Mode Switching (Studio / Design / Preview / Analyze)
- The mode rail (the icon-only left column) has no labels — users can't tell what each icon does
- Active state contrast is too subtle
- No animated transition between mode switches feels cheap

### 5. Typography & Color Issues
- Overuse of `text-zinc-500` for subtitles → everything blends into gray soup
- Section titles use `text-[15px]` — inconsistent with the rest of the app's font scale
- The accent color (`#b91c1c` red) appears everywhere but has no semantic meaning — it's on primary CTA, active states, and decoration all at once

